From ec662820c91ee739653bc59d31db379bffbd61d9 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Sushant Butta <sbutta@qti.qualcomm.com>
Date: Fri, 4 Jul 2025 14:59:40 +0530
Subject: [PATCH] UPSTREAM: DP: wifi: ath12k: DP: Add type subtype support for
 monitor direct(MD) mode

Monitor Direct (MD) filters are used to sniff specific non connected
client packets, which are configured through WMI command
(VDEV_FILTER_NEIGHBOR_RX_PACKETS_CMD).

With the Filter framework, Monitor direct (MD) TLV filters are
configured with type and subtype to get configured non connected client
packets.

The hardware provides the capability to configure status TLVs
and packet data TLVs through separate registers.
status TLV's are used to get PPDU status, and packet tlv are used
to get complete packet.

Patch-dependency:
	0405-0006-UPSTREAM-DP-wifi-ath12k-Add-type-subtype-support-for.patch
	0407-0002-UPSTREAM-DP-wifi-ath12k-enable-MD-filter-for-NAC-RSSI.patch

Signed-off-by: Sushant Butta <sbutta@qti.qualcomm.com>
